<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-01-03T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-01-03T00:00:00-05:00" n="225" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d225">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">Paris Peace Conf. 184.82/13½</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Chief of the Press Bureau</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_BRS1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Baker</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the Private Secretary
                                of the Secretary of State</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Kirk</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                                </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-01-03">January
                                    3, 1919</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p rend="flushleft">Subject: List of visitors.</p>
                        <list>
                            <label>1.</label>
                            <item>I spoke to the Commission the other morning in regard to giving a
                                daily list of the visitors who have called upon the Commissioners,
                                and the names of those with whom the Commissioners have held
                                conferences, so that the newspaper correspondents can have some idea
                                of what is going on. This suggestion was approved.</item>
                            <label>2.</label>
                            <item>Will it be convenient for you if we have an orderly call at 6.30
                                every evening for these reports? This is a system with which the
                                correspondents have become familiar in connection with visitors to
                                the White House at Washington.</item>
                        </list>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_BRS1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Ray Stannard Baker</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>